Job Description
• Coordinate projects &amp; attend meetings
• Monitor and manage progress of the project and work with various external and internal parties and ensure that committed deliverables are met on time and compliant to safety requirements.
• Check and ensure all installation works conform to project design specifications and contractual terms and conditions
• Ensure compliance with safety with all safety legal and regulatory requirements

Requirements&nbsp;
• Min ITE/ Higher Nitec/ Diploma in any Engineering discipline
• Fresh Grad welcome to apply
• Good writing and communication skills
• Proficient in MS Office
• Possess good interpersonal, analytical and organizing skills
• Experience in Electrical Engineering will be an advantage, but not compulsory
• Singaporean Citizen/ PR